      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "There was plenty to like about the resuming effort of KEAYANG TWEETYBIRD (3) when runner-up from this barrier in a higher-graded race at Bendigo last week, her first outing since a midfield finish to star mare Keayang Zahara in the Vicbred Super Series Final last November. Proven second-up so should strip fitter and has won two of three attempts at this distance. SPIRITED LASS (7) overcame a second row draw for a resuming win at Cranbourne last Sunday. Draws wide but should be improved. OFF YOUR FACESKI (2) has won second-up before so can improve after he led from this barrier and stuck on for a 2.3m second at Ballarat last week. MANDA KYVALLEY (6) found form with a 7.4m win at Melton last week. Draws wider but could go on with it with even luck.",
